    "html":  "\u003cdiv style=\"display:flex; align-items:flex-start; justify-content:space-between; flex-wrap:wrap; gap:12px; margin-bottom:24px;\"\u003e\n  \u003cdiv\u003e\n    \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:600; color:#60a5fa; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.8px; margin-bottom:6px;\"\u003eDaily Economic Briefing\u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003ch2 style=\"margin:0; font-size:20px; font-weight:700; color:#e2e8f0;\"\u003eWednesday, 08 July 2026\u003c/h2\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"display:flex; gap:8px; flex-wrap:wrap;\"\u003e\n    \u003cspan style=\"background:rgba(251,191,36,0.12); border:1px solid rgba(251,191,36,0.25); color:#fbbf24; padding:4px 12px; border-radius:6px; font-size:11px; font-weight:600;\"\u003eMOVE 70.25 Repricing\u003c/span\u003e\n    \u003cspan style=\"background:rgba(52,211,153,0.12); border:1px solid rgba(52,211,153,0.25); color:#34d399; padding:4px 12px; border-radius:6px; font-size:11px; font-weight:600;\"\u003eSOFR 3.63% Stable\u003c/span\u003e\n    \u003cspan style=\"background:rgba(96,165,250,0.12); border:1px solid rgba(96,165,250,0.25); color:#60a5fa; padding:4px 12px; border-radius:6px; font-size:11px; font-weight:600;\"\u003eNFCI \u0026#8722;0.504 Loose\u003c/span\u003e\n    \u003cspan style=\"background:rgba(248,113,113,0.12); border:1px solid rgba(248,113,113,0.25); color:#f87171; padding:4px 12px; border-radius:6px; font-size:11px; font-weight:600;\"\u003eFOMC 14:00 ET\u003c/span\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a1f2e; border:1px solid #2d3748; border-radius:12px; padding:20px; margin-bottom:20px;\"\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:600; color:#94a3b8; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.6px; margin-bottom:14px;\"\u003e\u0026#128202; Liquidity \u0026amp; Stress Metrics \u0026#8212; The \u0026quot;Gnosis\u0026quot; Pulse\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:12px; color:#64748b; line-height:1.6; margin-bottom:14px;\"\u003eCurrent regime: Structural Expansion, but with rate-volatility repricing after the holiday lull. Funding remains stable and broad financial conditions are still loose; today\u0026apos;s test is whether FOMC minutes and 10-year supply push MOVE back into a tighter-risk posture.\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"overflow-x:auto;\"\u003e\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; font-size:13px;\"\u003e\u003cthead\u003e\u003ctr style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #2d3748;\"\u003e\u003cth style=\"text-align:left; padding:8px 12px; color:#64748b; font-weight:600; text-transform:uppercase; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.5px;\"\u003eMetric\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"text-align:right; padding:8px 12px; color:#64748b; font-weight:600; text-transform:uppercase; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.5px;\"\u003eValue\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"text-align:left; padding:8px 12px; color:#64748b; font-weight:600; text-transform:uppercase; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.5px;\"\u003eMarket Context\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"text-align:center; padding:8px 12px; color:#64748b; font-weight:600; text-transform:uppercase; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.5px;\"\u003eStatus\u003c/th\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/thead\u003e\u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #1e293b;\"\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#e2e8f0; font-weight:500;\"\u003eMOVE Index\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; text-align:right; color:#fbbf24; font-weight:700;\"\u003e70.25\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:left;\"\u003eTreasury volatility lifted from the mid-60s into the low-70s. Still contained by historical standards, but no longer pure premium extinction.\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; text-align:center;\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"background:rgba(251,191,36,0.12); border:1px solid rgba(251,191,36,0.25); color:#fbbf24; padding:3px 10px; border-radius:6px; font-size:11px; font-weight:600;\"\u003eRate-Vol Repricing\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #1e293b;\"\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#e2e8f0; font-weight:500;\"\u003eSOFR Rate\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; text-align:right; color:#34d399; font-weight:700;\"\u003e3.63%\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:left;\"\u003eSecured overnight funding remains orderly after quarter-end and holiday effects. No plumbing stress signal from SOFR.\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; text-align:center;\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"background:rgba(52,211,153,0.12); border:1px solid rgba(52,211,153,0.25); color:#34d399; padding:3px 10px; border-radius:6px; font-size:11px; font-weight:600;\"\u003eStable\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#e2e8f0; font-weight:500;\"\u003eNFCI\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; text-align:right; color:#60a5fa; font-weight:700;\"\u003e\u0026#8722;0.504\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:left;\"\u003eLatest weekly NFCI remains negative, confirming looser-than-average financial conditions across risk, credit, and leverage channels.\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; text-align:center;\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"background:rgba(96,165,250,0.12); border:1px solid rgba(96,165,250,0.25); color:#60a5fa; padding:3px 10px; border-radius:6px; font-size:11px; font-weight:600;\"\u003eLoose\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"margin-top:16px; padding:14px 16px; background:rgba(96,165,250,0.06); border-left:3px solid #60a5fa; border-radius:0 8px 8px 0;\"\u003e\n    \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:10px; font-weight:700; color:#60a5fa; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.6px; margin-bottom:6px;\"\u003eGnosis Interpretation\u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:13px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003eThe liquidity floor remains intact because SOFR is stable and NFCI is loose, but MOVE at 70.25 says rate traders are no longer asleep. Today\u0026apos;s structural risk is a duration repricing around the 10-year reopening and FOMC minutes, not a funding break. Keep the equity-bullish regime, but require cleaner absorption around rates events.\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a1f2e; border:1px solid #2d3748; border-radius:12px; padding:20px; margin-bottom:20px;\"\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:600; color:#94a3b8; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.6px; margin-bottom:14px;\"\u003e\u0026#128197; Economic Calendar: 2026-07-08\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:12px; color:#64748b; line-height:1.6; margin-bottom:14px;\"\u003eBuilt from US 2-/3-star market-calendar events and primary-source checks. Census confirms May wholesale trade at 10:00 ET, EIA confirms weekly petroleum data at 10:30 ET, TreasuryDirect lists the 10-year reopening auction today, and the Fed calendar points to FOMC minutes from the June meeting.\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"overflow-x:auto;\"\u003e\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; font-size:13px;\"\u003e\u003cthead\u003e\u003ctr style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #2d3748;\"\u003e\u003cth style=\"text-align:left; padding:8px 12px; color:#64748b; font-weight:600; text-transform:uppercase; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.5px;\"\u003eEvent\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"text-align:center; padding:8px 12px; color:#64748b; font-weight:600; text-transform:uppercase; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.5px;\"\u003eEST (US)\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"text-align:center; padding:8px 12px; color:#64748b; font-weight:600; text-transform:uppercase; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.5px;\"\u003eGMT+8 (Local)\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"text-align:center; padding:8px 12px; color:#64748b; font-weight:600; text-transform:uppercase; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.5px;\"\u003eImportance\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"text-align:left; padding:8px 12px; color:#64748b; font-weight:600; text-transform:uppercase; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.5px;\"\u003eNotes\u003c/th\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/thead\u003e\u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #1e293b;\"\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#e2e8f0;\"\u003eUS May Wholesale Trade: Sales and Inventories\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:center;\"\u003e10:00\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:center;\"\u003e22:00\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; text-align:center;\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"color:#fbbf24; font-weight:600; font-size:12px;\"\u003eMedium\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#64748b; font-size:12px;\"\u003eInventory/sales mix feeds GDP tracking and margin pressure. Watch whether inventory accumulation looks demand-led or defensive.\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #1e293b;\"\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#e2e8f0;\"\u003eEIA Weekly Petroleum Status Report / Crude Inventories\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:center;\"\u003e10:30\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:center;\"\u003e22:30\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; text-align:center;\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"color:#f87171; font-weight:600; font-size:12px;\"\u003eMedium-High\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#64748b; font-size:12px;\"\u003eEnergy inventory shock window. Crude, gasoline, distillates, and Cushing can reprice inflation breakevens and cyclicals.\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #1e293b;\"\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#e2e8f0;\"\u003eUS 10-Year Note Reopening Auction\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:center;\"\u003e13:00\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:center;\"\u003e01:00 (+1)\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; text-align:center;\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"color:#f87171; font-weight:600; font-size:12px;\"\u003eHigh\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#64748b; font-size:12px;\"\u003eTreasuryDirect lists a $39B 9-year 10-month reopening. Tail/stop strength is the key duration-risk input before FOMC minutes.\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #1e293b;\"\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#e2e8f0;\"\u003eFOMC Minutes: June 16-17 Meeting\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:center;\"\u003e14:00\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:center;\"\u003e02:00 (+1)\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; text-align:center;\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"color:#f87171; font-weight:600; font-size:12px;\"\u003eHigh\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#64748b; font-size:12px;\"\u003eLook for discussion around inflation persistence, balance-sheet posture, dissent risk, and whether the statement/minutes format reduces forward guidance.\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#e2e8f0;\"\u003eUS May Consumer Credit\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:center;\"\u003e15:00\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:center;\"\u003e03:00 (+1)\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; text-align:center;\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"color:#fbbf24; font-weight:600; font-size:12px;\"\u003eMedium\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#64748b; font-size:12px;\"\u003eLate-day household-credit read. Matters most if revolving credit growth clashes with the soft-landing consumer narrative.\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a1f2e; border:1px solid #2d3748; border-radius:12px; padding:20px; margin-bottom:20px;\"\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:600; color:#94a3b8; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.6px; margin-bottom:14px;\"\u003e\u0026#127963;\u0026#65039; Geopolitical \u0026amp; Fed Watch\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(251,191,36,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(251,191,36,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:14px 16px; margin-bottom:12px;\"\u003e\u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:700; color:#fbbf24; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.5px; margin-bottom:10px;\"\u003eFOMC Minutes: Policy-Path Clarity Test\u003c/div\u003e\u003cul style=\"margin:0; padding-left:18px; font-size:13px;\"\u003e\u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:8px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRates Lens:\u003c/strong\u003e Minutes arrive after the 10-year reopening, so rates desks get two duration catalysts in sequence. A less informative minutes format still matters if it confirms a higher-for-longer bias.\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:8px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eEquity Lens:\u003c/strong\u003e ES can tolerate hawkish language if yields and MOVE stay contained. A rate-vol spike after 14:00 ET is the signal that equity breadth may need to de-risk.\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(96,165,250,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(96,165,250,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:14px 16px; margin-bottom:12px;\"\u003e\u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:700; color:#60a5fa; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.5px; margin-bottom:10px;\"\u003eEnergy \u0026amp; Inflation Channel\u003c/div\u003e\u003cul style=\"margin:0; padding-left:18px; font-size:13px;\"\u003e\u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:8px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eInventory Risk:\u003c/strong\u003e EIA petroleum data can move crude, gasoline, and breakevens before the Fed minutes. Treat energy as the intraday bridge between inflation narrative and rates.\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:8px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eGeopolitical Discipline:\u003c/strong\u003e Use confirmed energy/inventory data over unverified geopolitical claims. The market is trading realized supply conditions, not narrative alone.\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a1f2e; border:1px solid #2d3748; border-radius:12px; padding:20px; margin-bottom:20px;\"\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:600; color:#94a3b8; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.6px; margin-bottom:14px;\"\u003e\u0026#128200; Trading Strategy Note (ES Futures)\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(52,211,153,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(52,211,153,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:12px 16px; margin-bottom:10px; font-size:13px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe Breakout Blueprint:\u003c/strong\u003e Structural liquidity remains supportive, but today is not a clean drift session. The ES long bias survives only if 10-year supply and FOMC minutes do not trigger a sustained rate-vol breakout.\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(96,165,250,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(96,165,250,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:12px 16px; margin-bottom:10px; font-size:13px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTarget Horizons:\u003c/strong\u003e Keep the structural upside map intact, but respect intraday two-way risk around 13:00 and 14:00 ET. A clean auction plus benign minutes can re-open expansion; a weak auction plus hawkish minutes can force a tactical reset.\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(251,191,36,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(251,191,36,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:12px 16px; margin-bottom:10px; font-size:13px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eOrder-Flow Execution:\u003c/strong\u003e Monitor 1.5k MotiveWave volume charts around 10:00 ET wholesale data, 10:30 ET EIA, 13:00 ET 10-year auction, and 14:00 ET FOMC minutes. Do not buy first-touch VAL flushes blindly; wait for absorption after rates settle.\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(148,163,184,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(148,163,184,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:12px 16px; margin-bottom:10px; font-size:13px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe Session Shape:\u003c/strong\u003e Expect clustered liquidity rather than smooth trend. Best trades should appear after event windows define whether MOVE is merely repricing or beginning a broader volatility impulse.\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e"
